<HEAD>15 Feared Dead, 7 Injured in Storm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A storm packing winds of up to 60 miles per hour capsized scores of small fishing boats, flattened hundreds of mud and straw huts and at least 15 people were feared dead, police said Sunday. Rescue workers searched the banks of the <LOCATION> Jamuna </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> on Sunday for survivors of the Friday storm in <LOCATION> Mankiganj </LOCATION> <LOCATION> District </LOCATION>, northwest of <LOCATION> Dhaka </LOCATION>, officials said. `` We see slim chances that the missing are still surviving,'' said a police official in <LOCATION> Manikganj </LOCATION>, who spoke in a telephone interview on condition of anonymity. He said no bodies had yet been recovered. The storm along the river was slow in being reported because the wind also damaged electrical and telephone wires in the region. More than 300 mud and straw huts were flattened, and trees and crops damaged, officials said. More than 50 fishing boats were believed capsized or sunk.
