<TEXT>
 A man who said his hearing was damaged when a <ORGANIZATION> Lufthansa </ORGANIZATION> airline attendant spilled hot drinks over his head has won nearly $ 40,000 in damages, a newspaper reported Sunday. The plaintiff, a <LOCATION> Bahraini </LOCATION> lawyer identified as <PERSON> Abdul-Wahab </PERSON> <PERSON> Ahmed </PERSON> <PERSON> bin </PERSON> <PERSON> Harmas </PERSON>, had filed the suit against the West German airline in <LOCATION> Bahrain </LOCATION>'s High Civil Court. The lawsuit alleged negligence and said the flight attendant accidentally spilled four pots of hot coffee and tea over his head, according to the English-language Gulf Daily News. The newspaper said the court awarded him 15,000 dinars, or $ 39,750, which was one-tenth the amount sought. The paper said the accident occurred during a flight from <LOCATION> Frankfurt </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Bahrain </LOCATION>, when the plane hit severe turbulence. It gave no precise dates. The man's injuries led to three months' treatment in <LOCATION> Bahrain </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, the newspaper said. The court ruled that it was the airline's responsibility to ensure the safety of passengers, the paper said. <ORGANIZATION> Lufthansa </ORGANIZATION> officials in <LOCATION> Bahrain </LOCATION> have refused to comment on the case.
