<HEAD>Soviet Paper Hints Police Erred In Ending Hijack</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> MOSCOW </LOCATION> _ A newspaper Sunday questioned whether officials acted properly by ordering a hijacked <ORGANIZATION> Aeroflot </ORGANIZATION> jet to land on Soviet territory, pointing out that nine people were killed, 19 injured and the plane burned to ashes. An 11-member family jazz band from the Siberian city of <LOCATION> Irkutsk </LOCATION> seized the plane on Tuesday as it headed across the <LOCATION> Ural </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mountains </LOCATION>, Soviet reports said. They demanded to be flown to <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>. The Aeroflot crew duped the air pirates into believing they were landing in <LOCATION> Finland </LOCATION>, but set down at a small airstrip near <LOCATION> Leningrad </LOCATION>. The hijackers, led by a matriarch in her 50s who had been honored as a Hero-Mother of the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>, shot and killed a stewardess when they realized they had been deceived and set off a bomb after two hours of negotiations when a police assault team stormed the plane. Five of the hijackers were killed, Soviet reports said. Sunday's edition of <ORGANIZATION> Komsomolskaya </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pravda </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> youth newspaper, said the hijackers would have faced trial in <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> if their demands to be flown there had been granted. `` We are entitled to a question: was n't the price too costly for the decision to detain the bandits on our territory?'' the newspaper asked. `` An answer to this question lies with the courts.'' In calculating the cost of the incident, <ORGANIZATION> Komsomolskaya </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pravda </ORGANIZATION> said `` the aircraft burned to ashes, nine people, including five of the criminals, were killed, and 19 people, including two on the assault team, were wounded, and many will be crippled for life.'' Previous reports said the hijackers