called the <ORGANIZATION> Quick </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reaction </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Team </ORGANIZATION>, which specialized in electronic surveillance, according to <LOCATION> Emerson </LOCATION>. The agents initially tried to bug <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>'s luxurious residence, but they were scared off by barking dogs and guards who opened fire, the book says. `` Another attempt met with better results,'' the report said. `` QRT agents succeeded in planting a bug in a lavish <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> apartment. But six tapes, each 90 minutes long, failed to yield any significant intelligence on <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>.'' The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> is now applying massive economic sanctions, including a freeze on <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>'s bank assets, in an effort to force <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>'s resignation. The general also has been indicted on drug charges by a federal grand jury. Other findings from <LOCATION> Emerson </LOCATION>'s book include: _ <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION> officials negotiated with the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> and Libyan intermediaries to obtain the release of Americans being held in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>, according to classified portions of private notebooks of fired Marine Lt. Col. <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> <PERSON> North </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> aide who was a central figure in the Iran-Contra affair. One plan, which later collapsed, called for $ 10 million in covert payments to <PERSON> Sheik </PERSON> <PERSON> Fadlallah </PERSON>, the leader of the <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION> organization holding the hostages and <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON> <PERSON> Massawi </PERSON>, the leader of the Islamic Amal militia. At <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> reque